            <description><![CDATA[
<h2>What's New</h2>

<h3>Changed</h3>
<ul>
<li>Rebuilt and verified against Xcode 27 / macOS 27 (build and full test suite pass on the new SDK).</li>
</ul>

<h3>Fixed</h3>
<ul>
<li>Two environment-dependent test failures: `returnsNilForUnknownModel` raced the live LiteLLM pricing map (which now legitimately prices `gpt-4`) and asserts the static fallback instead; `initialStateIsCorrect` leaked the real app's cached usage snapshot from the shared UserDefaults domain and now stashes and restores it.</li>
</ul>

See <a href="https://github.com/tartinerlabs/ClaudeMeter/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md">CHANGELOG.md</a> for full details.
            ]]></description>
